Description: A very nice colored tracker system for everything from coins and imbues looted to rooms moved and kills per day!

Contains: 3 triggers & 1 alias

Usage: A veritable superscript(nearly a thousand lines of code) which tracks herbs picked, kills, imbues looted, coins looted, your progress to your next mortal level, your rooms moved, and even the money in your bank account! It 
       It takes a bit of a while to set up properly but once it's done, this is a very satisfying bit of code! 
       You can see everything you do update live, or if you're playing on mobile, type <trax> to see it in the conventional way.
       If you have coding experience, this should be fairly easy to set up with everything working, and if you don't have experience this is a good way to practice!! You don't actually have to code anything, just drop in my code to the right places.

!!! Credit to Faery for the tab addition code and to Exosphere for the browser storage code !!!

Note: The hunting and herbing progress trackers are made to be used with Exosphere's amazing superscripts! 
      Trax works without them, but it's incorporated into the script to show progress and status on them. 
      To track if your hunting/herbing scripts are enabled and their progress, drop in a simple line of code to the bit of the alias that enables it, and another into the trigger where it disables it! 
      Same with the pausing feature in the hunting script. Here are all the things to put in:

gwc.userdata.trax.huntonoff = "on"; //put in as a new line in the enable part of the hunting script
gwc.userdata.trax.huntonoff = "off";//put in the disable/ending part of the hunting script
gwc.userdata.trax.huntpaused == true //put in the pause section of the hunting script
gwc.userdata.trax.huntpaused == false //put in the resume section of the hunting script
gwc.userdata.trax.herbonoff = "on" //put in the start new path of the herbing alias
gwc.userdata.trax.herbonoff = "off" //put in the finish path section of the herbing trigger
gwc.userdata.healing = "on" //put in your auto heal script if you have them
gwc.userdata.healing = "on" //put in the end of your auto heal script

      Again, the script works completely fine without these, but they are automatically incorporated!

